<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE article  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.4//EN'  'http://www.docbook.org/xml/4.4/docbookx.dtd'><article><articleinfo><title>EliezerCroitoru/SSLtips</title><revhistory><revision><revnumber>3</revnumber><date>2016-06-13 18:36:35</date><authorinitials>AlexRousskov</authorinitials><revremark>Avoid &quot;real&quot; domains in examples [unless absolutely necessary], especially &quot;sensitive&quot; domains.</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>2</revnumber><date>2016-06-13 06:53:39</date><authorinitials>Eliezer Croitoru</authorinitials><revremark>Adding a certificate inspection command</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>1</revnumber><date>2014-07-04 03:26:16</date><authorinitials>Eliezer Croitoru</authorinitials></revision></revhistory></articleinfo><para>Describe EliezerCroitoru/SSLtips here. </para><para>You can take a look also at: <ulink url="http://www.sslshopper.com/article-most-common-openssl-commands.html"/> <!--The macro TableOfContents doesn't work with the DocBook formatter.--> </para><section><title>Couple handy commands with openssl</title><section><title>To verify a certificate or a key</title><para>To check a private key: </para><screen><![CDATA[openssl rsa -in privateKey.key -check]]></screen><para>To check a certificate: </para><screen><![CDATA[openssl x509 -in certificate.crt -text -noout]]></screen><para>To check a PKCS#12 file: </para><screen><![CDATA[openssl pkcs12 -info -in keyStore.p12]]></screen></section><section><title>Converting commands</title><para>From .der .crt .cer to .pem </para><screen><![CDATA[openssl x509 -inform der -in certificate.der -out certificate.pem]]></screen><para>From .pem to .der </para><screen><![CDATA[openssl x509 -outform der -in certificate.pem -out certificate.der]]></screen><para>from PKCS#12 file (.pfx .p12) to PEM </para><screen><![CDATA[openssl pkcs12 -in keyStore.pfx -out keyStore.pem -nodes]]></screen></section><section><title>Fetch X509v3 Subject Alternative Names and couple other properties</title><screen><![CDATA[echo ""|openssl s_client -connect www.example.com:443|openssl x509 -text -noout \
  -certopt no_subject,no_header,no_version,no_serial,no_signame,no_validity,no_subject,no_issuer,no_pubkey,no_sigdump,no_aux \
  | awk '/X509v3 Subject Alternative Name/','/X509v3 Basic Constraints/']]></screen></section></section></article>